
[1]indivisible

   INDIVIS'IBLE, a. s as z. [in and divisible. See Divide.]

   That cannot be divided, separated or broken; not separable into parts.
   Perhaps the particles of matter, however small, cannot be considered as
   indivisible. The mind or soul must be indivisible. A mathematical point
   is indivisible.

   INDIVIS'IBLE, n. In geometry, indivisibles are the elements or
   principles into which a body or figure may be resolved; elements
   infinitely small.
